div.p: An algorithm that uses Graph theories to trace covid-19 contacts within establishments base on a given number of days.

In a graph, there are nodes and edges. Here, users are the nodes. They can be connected once they have been visited the same establishment within the same day. The connection is bidirectional and unweighted.
This algorithm will serve as an analysis engine for indetifying covid-19 treats and therefore produce interventions to control virus transmition and lessen the cases.

div.div:
Consider the graph above. Remember that each node/person has the information in their Contacts [ ] field.
The functions of the algorithm are the following
Trace the persons that are possibly socialized with the covid-positive. They are the immediate neighbouring nodes of covid-positive node.
Predict if their case is caused by another covid-positive node/s by exploring the graph base on the establishment they visit and the date and time they visited which is prior to the date of covid-positivity of the root node/person.

div.div:
In this case, person E is the covid-positive.
Person C and D are the closest contact.
With this information, we can trace if C and D has a previous case or history of covid-positivity. If none, we can trace their connections if they have been socialized with a covid positive prior to the date of positivity.
From person C and D, we can trace their edges using DFS or depth-first search algorithm to check if someone has been covid-positive within the date of Person E's date of covid-positivty.
Therefore, it can trace where the virus originated in the community and who are the ones that should undergo for covid-19 testing. The information will also be beneficial to an establishment for indentifying covid-19 transmition and immediate disinfection.

div.div:
1. Start from the root node (covid-positive node)
2. Get the date and time of positivity
3. Get the last visited establishment on that date
4. Traverse the graph is any of its branches has a previous covid case. We will check for the matching date and establishment of the root and the visiting node. Any matching nodes should be added to some sort of data structure such as Map or Object to trace the contact.
5. The Traversal will be recursive and the base case will be - if none of their neighboring nodes matches the said criteria.

div.div:
This project is focusing on the algorithm.
But, to test the algorithm and to prove it is working, researchers should create the system of how the data will be kept and processed.
We need the following tools.
1. The Contact tracing App
2. A server to process the data
3. A Database to store the data
4. App users will enter the establishment 7 digit code or Qr code if possible and make a call to a server to connect the visiting persons in the graph described in
Figure 1.1
5. A reporting website panel to report a covid positive. For each report, the tracing will automatically run and warn to branches of that covid-positive node. Reports are only available to subscribing companies proved by their employee's SWAB Test
6. An automatic warning of covid positivity.
